sentences: Choi Jung-in (Korean: 최정인; born December 7, 1980), also known mononymously as Jung-in, is a South Korean singer of Jungle Entertainment.
She debuted in Leessang's "Rush" and was once part of the five-member group G. Fla until disbanding after three years.
Her first album From Andromeda was released on March 11, 2010.
On April 5, she released Melody Remedy.
